<Link id="l00278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="278"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Prefixed instruction introduced in ISAv3.1 consists of two 32-bit words,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// prefix word and suffix word, i.e., prefixed&#95;instruction = concat(prefix&#95;word,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// suffix&#95;word). That&#39;s to say, for a prefixed instruction encoded in uint64&#95;t,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the most significant 32 bits belong to the prefix word. The prefix word is at</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// low address for both big/little endian. Byte order in each word still follows</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00283" /><CodeLine lineNumber="283"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// its endian.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="284"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;llvm::endianness Endianness&gt;</span></CodeLine>
